\title{Closure}
\author{alex-nelson}
\import{notation}
\date{2025-12-12}
\taxon{definition}
\meta{source}{Munkres [[munkres-2000-topology]] Section 17}

\p{Let #{(X,\mathcal{T})} be a [[gt-0002]]. Let #{E\subset X}. We define the \define{Closure} of #{E} to be the set #{\closure{E}} equal to the intersection of all closed sets containing #{E},
##{\closure{E}:=\bigcap\{F\mid F\mbox{ is closed}, E\subset F\}.}}
\p{Note that other possible notations for the closure of #{E} includes #{\mathop{\textrm{Cl}}(E)}.}